BASE_URL                      = The base url of the portal. Ex: http://localhost:[PORT] in dev mode.
GH_API_KEY                    = GitHub API key to access sources information. (needed in development mode)
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_ENV           = The environment of the app. Ex: production, staging, development.
NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_ANALYTICS  = Google analytics key to track user activity. (optional)
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL           = NDE API url. Ex: https://api.data.niaid.nih.gov/v1 or https://api-staging.data.niaid.nih.gov/v1
NEXT_PUBLIC_STRAPI_API_URL    = API URL to access Strapi cms content.
NEXT_PUBLIC_AUTH_PROVIDERS    = Comma-separated list of auth providers to enable. Ex: "github,orcid"

# Dev-only mock auth mode (bypasses /user_info CORS dependency)
NEXT_PUBLIC_MOCK_AUTH_USER_INFO = Set to "true" to enable mock auth mode in development. In this mode, the app will use the following environment variables to mock an authenticated user.
NEXT_PUBLIC_MOCK_AUTH_PROVIDER = The auth provider to mock. Ex: "github"
NEXT_PUBLIC_MOCK_AUTH_USERNAME = The username of the mocked user. Ex: "dev-user"
NEXT_PUBLIC_MOCK_AUTH_NAME = The display name of the mocked user. Ex: "Dev User"
NEXT_PUBLIC_MOCK_AUTH_EMAIL = The email of the mocked user. Ex: "dev.user@example.org"
NEXT_PUBLIC_MOCK_AUTH_AVATAR_URL = The avatar URL of the mocked user. Ex: "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1?v=4"
NEXT_PUBLIC_MOCK_AUTH_ORGANIZATION = The organization of the mocked user. Ex: "NIAID Dev Environment"

